## AC Testbench Setup

This figure shows the AC analysis testbench used to evaluate the performance of the two-stage CMOS operational amplifier designed in Cadence Virtuoso.

The testbench includes:
- Differential AC input voltage source applied at the input terminals
- DC supply voltage (VDD = 1.8 V)
- Load capacitance connected at the output node
- Ground reference node
- Output measurement point for gain and phase response

An AC sweep analysis is performed to measure the open-loop gain, phase margin, and bandwidth of the operational amplifier.
